# Feature Spec Template

Before implementing any feature, write a spec in `tasks/[feature-name]-spec.md`.
This ensures edge cases are considered before touching any code.

## Spec structure
```markdown
# [Feature Name] Spec

## Overview
One paragraph describing what this feature does and why.

## User flows
Step by step — what the user does and what the app does in response.

## Screens
List every screen/view involved. For each:
- What data is displayed
- What actions are available
- Loading / empty / error states

## API endpoints
List every endpoint needed:
- METHOD /api/path — description
- Request body (if POST/PATCH)
- Response shape

## Data models
List every model needed with its fields and types.

## Edge cases
- What happens if the API fails?
- What if the list is empty?
- What if the user is unauthenticated mid-session?
- Any race conditions?

## Tasks
Ordered implementation checklist:
- [ ] Create model: `models/feature_model.dart`
- [ ] Create service: `data/feature_service.dart`
- [ ] Create controller + atom: `controllers/feature_controller.dart`
- [ ] Create view: `views/feature/feature_view.dart`
- [ ] Create sub-widgets: `widgets/feature/`
```

## Rules
- Always write the spec before writing any code
- Get spec approved before moving to implementation
- Tasks must be in dependency order — model before service, service before controller, controller before view
